## SSR and browser safety

Browser APIs MUST NOT be accessed:
- During import
- In top-level constants
- In the constructor
- Before plugin registration or mount

Use core helpers:

```typescript
isBrowser();
safeWindow();
safeDocument();
safeMatchMedia();
```

Importing any package MUST work in an SSR environment without DOM.

## Store registration

```typescript
// Inside register function
Alpine.store("my", {
  value: 0,
  increment() { this.value++; },
});

// Magic access
Alpine.magic("my", () => Alpine.store("my"));
```

## Directive registration

```typescript
Alpine.directive("my", (el, { expression, effect, cleanup }, { evaluateLater }) => {
  const evaluate = evaluateLater(expression);
  effect(() => { /* react to changes */ });
  cleanup(() => { /* teardown listeners */ });
});
```

## Directives MUST defer DOM mutations

Use `Alpine.nextTick` + `Alpine.mutateDom` when mutating DOM during `initTree`:

```typescript
Alpine.nextTick(() => {
  Alpine.mutateDom(() => { el.style.display = "none"; });
});
```

## Type augmentation

```typescript
declare global {
  namespace Alpine {
    interface Stores {
      my: ReturnType<typeof createMyStore>;
    }
    interface Magics<T> {
      $my: MyMagic;
    }
  }
}
```
